1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,795
[Ahmad] <i>Everything is too well-planned.</i>

2
00:00:03,878 --> 00:00:05,672
<i>Too clean.</i>

3
00:00:05,755 --> 00:00:10,760
<i>That means, there's only one hand</i>
<i>controlling you all.</i>

4
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:15,098
Which one of you is behind all of this?

5
00:00:15,181 --> 00:00:20,145
[in English] You are hereby placed
under preventive suspension.

6
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:21,396
[Marcus] <i>While I'm out of service,</i>

7
00:00:21,479 --> 00:00:24,566
<i>Major Allan Espina</i>
<i>will be your team leader.</i>

8
00:00:24,649 --> 00:00:25,900
[Lara] <i>Marcus doesn't trust me.</i>

9
00:00:25,984 --> 00:00:29,237
<i>How can I control him</i>
<i>if he doesn't trust me?</i>

10
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,321
[Raquel] <i>I get it, Lara.</i>

11
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,323
But the important thing is General.

12
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:34,034
I don't know
if I'm still doing the right thing.

13
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:35,452
[Lara] <i>Even children are getting hurt.</i>

14
00:00:35,535 --> 00:00:38,163
<i>I'm turning into the people</i>
<i>who killed my parents.</i>

15
00:00:38,246 --> 00:00:40,957
Whatever the General tells us to do,

16
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:44,085
that's what we'll do
because that's what's right.

17
00:00:44,169 --> 00:00:47,088
[Solares] Get ready.
In the following days,

18
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:48,715
the evidence against you
will be presented.

19
00:00:48,798 --> 00:00:51,426
[Madrigal] <i>We will never forget</i>
<i>your sacrifices.</i>

20
00:00:51,926 --> 00:00:54,387
[Jamilah] <i>My brother</i>
<i>taught me how to fight.</i>

21
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:56,306
Do you know someone
who would do this to you?

22
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:58,975
A lot of people.
Because I'm Datu Rahman's daughter.

23
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,312
[Marcus] <i>Someone tried to kidnap Jamilah.</i>

24
00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:03,271
[Usman] <i>What?!</i>

25
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:04,773
[Espina] <i>Jamilah, what happened?</i>

26
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:05,815
You know each other?

27
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:08,902
Yes, I met her when I saved Datu Rahman.

28
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:11,613
[Felix] <i>Marcus, you bastard.</i>

29
00:01:11,696 --> 00:01:13,948
<i>I almost had Jalil Abubakar.</i>

30
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:15,950
But you got in my way again.

31
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:19,204
He tasked us to manipulate
police assignments

32
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:22,082
- to protect the syndicate's transactions
- [gunshot blasts]

33
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:24,250
from inside the department.

34
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:26,127
[Valdez] <i>Datu Rahman is ruining</i>

35
00:01:26,211 --> 00:01:28,713
<i>one of our main supply chains.</i>

36
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:31,174
[Yulo] <i>We've also taken care</i>

37
00:01:31,257 --> 00:01:33,802
<i>of other Task Force Alpha members.</i>

38
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:36,805
<i>We framed Datu Rahman's syndicate</i>

39
00:01:36,888 --> 00:01:38,348
<i>as the perpetrators</i>

40
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:41,059
<i>so the police force</i>
<i>would turn against them.</i>

41
00:01:42,268 --> 00:01:45,438
<i>And while the entire NLEA is busy</i>

42
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:47,816
<i>hunting down Datu Rahman,</i>

43
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:51,152
<i>we will be able to do our jobs freely.</i>

44
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:53,154
[ominous music playing]

45
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:57,909
[mysterious theme music playing]

46
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,423
- After a long process,
- [camera shutters clicking]

47
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:16,511
our investigation shows

48
00:02:16,594 --> 00:02:21,599
that Datu Rahman Abubakar
was made into a fall guy

49
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:25,103
by the syndicates so they could continue

50
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:28,690
with their illegal operations
in the country.

51
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:35,321
And as our officials here said themselves,

52
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:38,491
they were the masterminds

53
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:40,368
in Colonel Del Mundo's assassination

54
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:44,581
because of an unfair splitting
of their money.

55
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:47,208
- [tense music playing]
- [camera shutters clicking]

56
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:48,960
[snickers]

57
00:02:49,043 --> 00:02:50,128
[sniffs]

58
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:55,592
[in English] Everything
is falling into place.

59
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:00,471
[Manuel snickers]

60
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:07,395
[Azuelo] <i>The syndicate still exists.</i>

61
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:11,399
- But I assure the public
- [camera shutters clicking]

62
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:16,195
that there are no more accomplices
inside the NLEA.

63
00:03:18,781 --> 00:03:20,366
As promised,

64
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:24,954
we will pursue and arrest these syndicates

65
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,165
to the best of our abilities.

66
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:30,752
[Azuelo] <i>We can do this much easier now</i>

67
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:33,463
<i>because we have cleaned up the agency.</i>

68
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:39,594
<i>There's no one left</i>
<i>to protect them from our ranks.</i>

69
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:44,474
[music intensifies]

70
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:46,017
[camera shutters clicking]

71
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,101
‪[dramatic sting]

72
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,561
‪[pensive music playing]

73
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:59,072
‪[intense music playing]

74
00:04:12,168 --> 00:04:13,253
[Marcus] <i>What do you think?</i>

75
00:04:14,462 --> 00:04:16,965
- It's too easy. Too clean.
- [intriguing music playing]

76
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:21,177
They said everything we wanted to hear.

77
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,721
That's what I think too.

78
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:27,600
The interrogation was too clean.

79
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:28,851
Too polished.

80
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:30,603
There are no holes.

81
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,522
As if they were following a script.

82
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:35,024
Could this all be a set-up?

83
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:39,612
[intriguing music playing]

84
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:41,489
But by who?

85
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:45,118
I have a hunch,

86
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:47,328
but I'm not sure.

87
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,206
Me, too.

88
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:54,127
I've yet to get any proof, but…

89
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,338
I think…

90
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,842
- it's General Carillo.
- It's General Carillo.

91
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:02,427
[dramatic music playing]

92
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:09,517
If General Carillo is the mastermind,

93
00:05:10,351 --> 00:05:12,228
that means we're against a strong enemy.

94
00:05:13,813 --> 00:05:16,524
The connection and influence
of the agency lies on him.

95
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,568
The general is smart.

96
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:21,112
He can toy with us if he wants to.

97
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:28,161
We need to find out his weaknesses.

98
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:31,164
In order to do that,

99
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,708
we have to find out
who's working with him.

100
00:05:36,252 --> 00:05:40,798
Actually, I've been keeping an eye

101
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,301
on his adoptive daughter, Lara.

102
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:47,013
I've been watching Lara for a long time.

103
00:05:47,972 --> 00:05:51,642
I just held off my suspicion
because we were friends.

104
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:55,229
But if General Carillo is behind this,

105
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:58,900
there's no way that Lara
didn't know about it.

106
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:01,319
That only means…

107
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:04,989
that this is bigger than we thought?

108
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:07,784
[suspenseful music playing]

109
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:13,372
Our fight is just about to begin.

110
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:18,336
[suspenseful music playing]

111
00:06:25,968 --> 00:06:29,931
[suspenseful music intensifies]

112
00:06:45,321 --> 00:06:47,949
Sir, there's something wrong
with what's happening.

113
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:51,911
I don't think it's over

114
00:06:51,994 --> 00:06:53,412
after Yulo and Valdez were arrested.

115
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:57,250
Major Espina shares the same sentiment.
I talked to him.

116
00:06:57,750 --> 00:07:01,087
We both think that they're just fall guys.

117
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:02,088
[disturbing music playing]

118
00:07:02,171 --> 00:07:03,673
What do you mean?

119
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:05,842
Sir, don't you find it weird?

120
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:09,303
They didn't even fight back
when they were arrested.

121
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:11,472
During the interrogation,

122
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:12,974
they just sat there

123
00:07:13,057 --> 00:07:16,144
and spilled everything they know.

124
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:18,521
Isn't that good?

125
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:20,106
They didn't give us a hard time.

126
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:22,066
Sir.

127
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:25,111
We're against a massive syndicate group.

128
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:28,072
Even notorious criminals
are scared of them.

129
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,824
They won't dare speak up when questioned

130
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:31,701
because of fear.

131
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:34,078
And now, two police officers
got arrested, betrayed them,

132
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:35,496
and confessed everything?

133
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,748
Didn't they get scared, sir?

134
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:41,043
What if we just really outsmarted them?

135
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:44,464
These syndicate groups make mistakes, too.

136
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:46,048
But, sir…

137
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:51,596
You know, I don't understand
Major Espina either.

138
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:53,598
Wasn't he the one who arrested those two?

139
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:57,977
Now that they've talked,

140
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:01,981
you're saying that their statements
aren't true.

141
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:06,319
Sir. We've been trying
to catch them for a long time.

142
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:08,738
We've chased after them multiple times,

143
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,740
but they always got away.

144
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:12,366
A lot of people have died,

145
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:14,660
including our colleagues.

146
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:17,205
And now you're telling me it's over

147
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:21,584
just because two police officers
decided to spill what they know?

148
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:24,837
You want me to just believe
and accept that as the truth?

149
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:26,047
[Azuelo] That's the point!

150
00:08:26,130 --> 00:08:29,759
We've been dealing
with this problem for a long time.

151
00:08:29,842 --> 00:08:32,553
We have been searching
for answers for a long time.

152
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:34,472
[in English] And now, this.

153
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:38,017
[in English] This is the product
of our hard work!

154
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:42,104
Why can't you accept that it's over?

155
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:44,232
Our side won.

156
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:46,234
[dramatic tense music playing]

157
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:48,444
You know, Agent Reyes,

158
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:52,990
you also acted this way
after your mission on Damai Island.

159
00:08:54,825 --> 00:08:57,036
But, sir, I was right
about that, wasn't I?

160
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:03,376
Sir, it's possible that this is
just a part of their bigger plan

161
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:05,711
to keep us from discovering the truth.

162
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:13,761
[in English] Fine! Okay!

163
00:09:15,304 --> 00:09:16,597
Why?

164
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:18,933
Who do you think is responsible for this?

165
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:20,977
Do you have a lead?

166
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,480
[music intensifies]

167
00:09:27,858 --> 00:09:29,819
It's General Carillo, sir.

168
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:30,736
‪[dramatic sting]

169
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:33,990
[in English] Goddammit!

170
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:35,032
[pensive music playing]

171
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:36,576
[in English] Goddammit, Reyes!

172
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:42,248
You're out of your mind!
What you're saying is impossible!

173
00:09:42,331 --> 00:09:45,042
Sir, nothing is impossible
with what's happening now.

174
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:46,085
You know that.

175
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:52,758
General Carillo was the one
who created the SID.

176
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:55,011
Everyone here respects him.

177
00:09:55,094 --> 00:09:57,430
And now you're telling me

178
00:09:57,513 --> 00:10:02,685
that he's sabotaging
the agency he built himself?!

179
00:10:04,228 --> 00:10:08,190
Reyes, you better not tell anyone that

180
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:11,861
if you don't want to get thrown
out of here for good!

181
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:17,617
[stirring music playing]

182
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:29,045
If you want me to believe you,

183
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:33,966
bring me solid evidence.

184
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:38,387
But until then,
we'll stick to the official findings.

185
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:42,058
We'll consider Yulo and Valdez

186
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:46,145
as the traitors within our ranks.

187
00:10:46,228 --> 00:10:47,355
[in English] Case solved!

188
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:52,068
The Philippines is safe.
The NLEA is clean.

189
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,737
Is that clear, Agent Reyes?

190
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,656
[melancholic music playing]

191
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:01,327
- But, sir…
- [Azuelo] Agent Reyes.

192
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:03,537
We're done discussing this.

193
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:05,247
I'm tired.

194
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:07,500
[in English] Take this as a win.

195
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:09,251
For now.

196
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:11,671
Stop overthinking it.

197
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:16,175
[stirring music continues]

198
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:18,928
[Azuelo] Goddammit!

199
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:21,222
[Azuelo sighs]

200
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:29,814
[stirring music continues]

201
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:30,731
‪[dramatic sting]

202
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:40,491
[reporter] General Villanueva, sir,

203
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:44,495
now that it's been proven
there were traitors within the NLEA,

204
00:11:44,578 --> 00:11:48,165
many fear that our foreign
business partners may pull back

205
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:49,750
because of this scandal.

206
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:52,503
How can you assure them and the public

207
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:55,297
that the country's security
remains under control?

208
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:58,884
[in English] Well, now
we are turning over a new leaf.

209
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:03,639
As we work to restore
public trust in the NLEA,

210
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:08,686
I'm also pleased to announce
that you have nothing to worry about.

211
00:12:09,353 --> 00:12:12,898
Our Japanese investment deal
is moving forward as planned.

212
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:15,192
<i>And in the coming days,</i>

213
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:18,154
<i>you can expect</i>
<i>an increased police visibility</i>

214
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,613
<i>throughout Metro Manila.</i>

215
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:23,409
<i>We're doing this to completely eliminate</i>

216
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:25,244
<i>the remaining criminal elements</i>

217
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:31,208
<i>and to help our citizens</i>
<i>feel safe in their communities.</i>

218
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:34,003
<i>Because the NLEA is still here,</i>

219
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:38,257
<i>ready to serve and protect.</i>

220
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,469
Your plan worked, General.

221
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:43,304
They bought it completely.

222
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:46,265
Even Villanueva immediately approved

223
00:12:46,348 --> 00:12:47,683
your request
for increased police visibility.

224
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:48,601
[Manuel chuckling]

225
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:50,644
Of course, they bought it.

226
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:52,938
I know exactly how they think. [inhales]

227
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:57,860
[exhales] The moment they're
convinced everything is quiet…

228
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:01,405
That's when we'll make our next move.

229
00:13:02,072 --> 00:13:03,491
Just a bit more…

230
00:13:04,074 --> 00:13:05,659
Our plan is almost complete.

231
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:08,078
[Madrigal] When that happens,

232
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:11,373
the NLEA and the rest
of the government institutions

233
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:13,417
will lose all credibility.

234
00:13:14,168 --> 00:13:17,838
[in English] And then… we seize power.

235
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:19,798
[music intensifies]

236
00:13:21,842 --> 00:13:22,676
‪[dramatic sting]

237
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,516
Looks like Datu Rahman
will finally be released.

238
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:32,228
You'll finally get justice
for your family and your fellow villagers.

239
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:35,814
Does this mean your mission is over?

240
00:13:36,857 --> 00:13:37,900
Not yet, Usman.

241
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:39,902
[tense music playing]

242
00:13:40,528 --> 00:13:41,403
Why?

243
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:42,321
[knocking on door]

244
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:45,866
[tense music playing]

245
00:13:48,118 --> 00:13:49,453
- [Usman] Buddy.
- [Espina] Reyes.

246
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:51,747
Reyes.

247
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,627
Director Azuelo doesn't believe me.

248
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:00,464
About what?

249
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:04,301
Marcus and I think Valdez and Yulo's case

250
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:07,137
are just part
of the syndicate's bigger plan.

251
00:14:08,764 --> 00:14:12,393
And General Carillo
is the one behind all this.

252
00:14:14,853 --> 00:14:16,855
But we don't have proof yet.

253
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:18,440
Wait.

254
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:22,528
So, you don't believe
Major Yulo and Captain Valdez?

255
00:14:23,112 --> 00:14:25,906
And you're suspecting General Carillo?

256
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,449
[tense music continues]

257
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,911
- That's a serious accusation.
- [Espina] Yes.

258
00:14:31,495 --> 00:14:32,955
So we have to be vigilant.

259
00:14:34,331 --> 00:14:37,251
The syndicate's moves are getting bolder.

260
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:39,128
Especially now

261
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:42,047
that the public believes
the NLEA has been cleaned up.

262
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:46,343
They're definitely planning
something bigger.

263
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:49,972
Does this mean…

264
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:52,474
the problem isn't really over yet?

265
00:14:53,976 --> 00:14:56,186
[music intensifies]

266
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,405
- Manuel.
- [Manuel] Mm.

267
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:08,699
What are you up to?

268
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:12,536
What exactly are you planning?

269
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:13,954
[chuckles, inhales deeply]

270
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:17,750
Well… [exhales] Dante…

271
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:21,170
[in English] Let me surprise you.

272
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:23,505
- [laughing]
- [dramatic sting]

273
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:32,222
[dramatic stinging]

274
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:33,891
‪[dramatic sting]

275
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:39,772
Why did you have
Jamilah Abubakar kidnapped?

276
00:15:39,855 --> 00:15:40,940
[in English] Are you crazy?!

277
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:41,941
[disturbing music playing]

278
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:42,900
[Felix] Because…

279
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:46,153
- she's Jalil Abubakar's sister.
- [Lara] And?

280
00:15:46,236 --> 00:15:47,696
They're both Datu Rahman's children!

281
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:50,574
So what? Datu Rahman
is already in Mustapha's custody!

282
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:53,661
[sighs] I already told you, didn't I?

283
00:15:54,328 --> 00:15:56,246
I just wanted to use that woman

284
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,958
to force Jalil Abubakar out of hiding.

285
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:02,920
But then Marcus got in the way
and ruined my plan!

286
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:04,296
[in English] You're so reckless!

287
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:06,674
[in English] You're so reckless!

288
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:10,928
Marcus is already suspicious of us,
and you're making it worse!

289
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:13,305
You're going to get us caught!

290
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:16,809
Stop your obsession with Jalil Abubakar!

291
00:16:17,893 --> 00:16:20,062
[scoffs] Madam, have you forgotten?

292
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:24,233
Wasn't it you who was obsessed
with Datu Rahman first?

293
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:25,818
Oh, and so?

294
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:27,611
Does that excuse what you did?

295
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,321
[Felix sighs]

296
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:31,532
[in English] Dad told us
we are this close to winning.

297
00:16:31,615 --> 00:16:33,033
[in English] Now is not the time
to go rogue.

298
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:34,994
Fine.

299
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:36,704
[tense music playing]

300
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:38,831
But Madam…

301
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:42,001
you should remind yourself of that first.

302
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:45,004
[dramatic sting]

303
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:56,724
I'm glad the real culprits
have finally been caught.

304
00:16:57,725 --> 00:17:01,895
I hope it keeps going like this,
so our father can finally come back to us.

305
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:05,649
I believe you'll be with your father soon.

306
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:07,192
Your brother, too.

307
00:17:07,776 --> 00:17:08,819
[chuckles softly]

308
00:17:08,902 --> 00:17:09,903
[in Arabic] God willing.

309
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:11,655
[phone ringing]

310
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:12,614
Oh.

311
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:15,617
Doctor, I'll just take this call.
Excuse me.

312
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:19,997
Jalil.

313
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:22,207
Jamilah, how are you?

314
00:17:22,916 --> 00:17:25,085
Did you notice anything unusual?

315
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:26,670
[Jalil] <i>Is anyone watching you?</i>

316
00:17:27,337 --> 00:17:28,464
No.

317
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:31,592
Uncle Omar and Auntie Norhana
brought me here earlier.

318
00:17:31,675 --> 00:17:34,636
They'll pick me up after my shift too.

319
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:35,888
Good.

320
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,140
It's dangerous if you're alone.

321
00:17:38,766 --> 00:17:41,852
[Jamilah sighs] <i>Jalil, don't worry.</i>

322
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:44,104
I can take care of myself.

323
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:46,815
I learned how to fight
from the best teacher.

324
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:51,570
- Jamilah.
- [Jamilah] <i>I'm just kidding, Jalil.</i>

325
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:54,490
I'm being careful. Don't worry.

326
00:17:56,408 --> 00:18:00,037
Jalil… I saw the news.

327
00:18:00,537 --> 00:18:03,165
Does this mean Father
is really cleared now?

328
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:04,666
Is he safe?

329
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,960
[pensive music playing]

330
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:10,214
[sighs deeply]

331
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:14,051
There are still processes to go through.

332
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,303
An investigation will be conducted.

333
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:21,725
But Jamilah, what matters is,
Father's name has been cleared.

334
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:25,229
[Jamilah] Just a little more,

335
00:18:25,312 --> 00:18:28,107
and we can go back to our old life.

336
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,150
We'll be with Father again.

337
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:34,029
- [in Arabic] God willing.
- [in Arabic] God willing.

338
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:35,781
[stirring music playing]

339
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:38,992
[exhales deeply]

340
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,877
<i>The Presidential Chief of Staff,</i>
<i>Ahmad Mustapha,</i>

341
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:51,880
<i>has released a statement</i>

342
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:55,968
<i>after the revelation</i>
<i>at the press conference of NLEA.</i>

343
00:18:56,051 --> 00:18:57,553
<i>According to Mustapha,</i>

344
00:18:57,636 --> 00:19:00,889
<i>Datu Rahman will officially be released</i>

345
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:05,060
<i>after being acquitted from all the cases</i>
<i>that were filed against him.</i>

346
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:07,729
<i>Since it was found</i>
<i>that he had no involvement</i>

347
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:10,357
<i>with the trafficking of illegal arms,</i>

348
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:13,235
<i>he wasn't required to testify.</i>

349
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:16,155
[in Arabic] Thanks to Allah!

350
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:18,740
<i>Mustapha also added</i>

351
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:21,535
<i>that instead of criticizing Datu Rahman,</i>

352
00:19:21,618 --> 00:19:24,121
<i>people should thank him</i>

353
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:28,667
<i>for preventing the distribution</i>
<i>of illegal firearms on their island.</i>

354
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,294
[pensive music playing]

355
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:32,838
<i>In line with this, the authorities</i>

356
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:35,174
<i>have officially halted the search</i>

357
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:37,885
<i>for Datu Rahman's son, Jalil Abubakar,</i>

358
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:39,428
<i>after it was proven</i>

359
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:43,682
<i>that all the allegations against</i>
<i>him were not true.</i>

360
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:46,268
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

361
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:54,443
[glass shatters]

362
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,998
[screams]

363
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:28,185
[in Arabic] Praise be to God!
Praise be to God!

364
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:30,354
Thank you!

365
00:20:30,437 --> 00:20:32,105
- [pensive music playing]
- [sighs]

366
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,108
Why are you crying?

367
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:37,611
Shouldn't you be happy?

368
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:39,321
I'm really happy,

369
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:43,200
but I'm just thinking about my friends.

370
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:45,661
I won't be able to tell them

371
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:48,664
that Datu Rahman will come back

372
00:20:48,747 --> 00:20:50,749
because they're all dead.

373
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:52,668
Oh…

374
00:20:52,751 --> 00:20:55,504
Those damn cops.

375
00:20:56,004 --> 00:20:58,340
A lot of innocent people
died because of them.

376
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,634
[Omar sighs]

377
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:03,637
[Rashid] Sitti, don't worry.

378
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,931
Justice will be served.

379
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:08,016
Just have faith.

380
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:09,434
Hmm?

381
00:21:10,143 --> 00:21:11,478
[pensive music continues]

382
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:13,146
[Norhana sniffles]

383
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:17,192
[Norhana] Datu Rahman will come back.

384
00:21:20,195 --> 00:21:22,197
Are we the only ones thinking like this?

385
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:26,118
Are we just messing things up?

386
00:21:26,201 --> 00:21:27,953
[tense sinister music playing]

387
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:31,415
You're the best investigator here.

388
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:34,209
What does your instinct say?

389
00:21:35,502 --> 00:21:37,254
I know that they're lying.

390
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:39,172
They're misleading us.

391
00:21:40,048 --> 00:21:43,635
But as long
as we don't have solid evidence,

392
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:45,429
no one will believe us.

393
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:47,931
That's why we're in this situation.

394
00:21:48,432 --> 00:21:51,768
[sighs] We still don't know
who's behind it.

395
00:21:53,061 --> 00:21:55,230
If our suspicion is true…

396
00:21:57,733 --> 00:22:00,694
justice hasn't been served

397
00:22:01,903 --> 00:22:03,613
to the people who died on Damai Island.

398
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:07,534
That's why we need to put an end to it.

399
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:13,123
I also don't want the death
of my friends to go in vain.

400
00:22:13,206 --> 00:22:15,167
[stirring music playing]

401
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:40,108
We're just making them believe
that their plans are working.

402
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:42,652
You're also suspicious of General Carillo?

403
00:22:42,736 --> 00:22:44,988
Lara has something to do with it.

404
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:46,448
Three days from now,

405
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:49,534
the high-level conference

406
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:52,245
for the Japanese investment deal
will take place.

407
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:55,082
The task force will provide security.

408
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:57,709
Since when did Task Force Alpha
become a security detail?

409
00:22:57,793 --> 00:22:58,835
We are not bodyguards.

410
00:22:58,919 --> 00:23:01,213
[in English] As the head agent,
I have to agree with Agent Reyes.

411
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:05,342
Datu Rahman has been proven innocent.

412
00:23:05,425 --> 00:23:07,219
I hope that it all ends here.

413
00:23:07,302 --> 00:23:09,513
[Azuelo] <i>Datu Rahman</i>
<i>might have been found innocent,</i>

414
00:23:09,596 --> 00:23:12,349
<i>but his life is still in danger.</i>

415
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:16,728
<i>So we need to protect him</i>
<i>while he's here in NLEA.</i>

416
00:23:17,354 --> 00:23:19,898
[man] <i>We only have one chance.</i>

417
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:23,777
<i>If we shoot him, make sure he's dead.</i>

418
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:25,278
[gunshots blasting]

419
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:29,157
[action music playing]
